The travel warning is also a response to a new Missouri law that makes it harder to sue a business for discrimination when renting or hiring.
The American Civil Liberties Union (ACLU) previously issued travel advisories for Texas and Arizona after those states passed immigration enforcement laws that ordered local law enforcement to arrest people for immigration violations, which the ACLU says will increase enforcement based on race.
Travel warnings are usually issued by the State Department for other countries, but recently advocacy groups have resorted to this practice in response to a number of laws and trends within the United States.
