You did it for a reason".
Then the audience sits down to dinner with the actors.
At a table, a white couple from Atlanta is having a passionate conversation about rejuvenation with a black couple.
Denise Duplinski is having trouble finding words to describe how the performance made her feel.
He said, "Hearing these horrible, horrible words and these behaviors... come from people like you and they do it because they look like you".
"What it does to me is make me think that the lynchings are still going on", he added, "these are just called police gun attacks anymore".
At the end of the room, Tyrone Brooks is the center of attention at the table, eating and talking about his civil rights memories.
He said he's already started planning his performance for next year.
He said: "The revival is inspiring in a way because it describes what we have endured but it is also instructive".
"Like if you don't learn from it, it could happen again.
Those who do not investigate their own past, those who do not know their own past, are doomed to repeat it".
